===================================================
pieces.py — The kit bash library

Walls (flat, with window cutout, with door cutout)
Floor/ceiling slabs
Roof types (flat, angled)
Stairs, railings
Simple furniture (couch, table, bed)

builder.py — Core placement logic

Place a piece at a grid position
Snap pieces to each other
Rotate/mirror pieces
Randomize material colors/finishes

scene_manager.py — File I/O

Save current layout to a JSON file
Load a saved layout and rebuild it in Maya
Clear the scene

validator.py — Error handling & input validation

Check for overlapping pieces
Validate grid positions
Warn on missing inputs

ui.py — The Maya window

Buttons for each piece type
Grid coordinate inputs
Save/Load buttons
A "randomize finishes" button
